Talks Held between Information Delegations of DPRK and Nepal 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- Talks between the delegation of the DPRK Information Committee and the Nepalese government information delegation were held at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Monday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there from the DPRK side were members of the delegation of the DPRK Information Committee headed by its Chairman Kang Nung Su, minister of Culture, and from the opposition side members of the Nepalese government information delegation headed by Krishna Bahadur Mahara, minister of Information and Communications of Nepal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the talks both sides exchanged views on boosting the friendly and cooperative relations between the two information organizations and a series of matters of mutual concern. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The talks proceeded in a friendly atmosphere.

4th Pyongyang Autumn International Trade Fair Opens 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- The 4th Pyongyang Autumn International Trade Fair was opened with due ceremony at the Three-Revolution Exhibition on Monday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Present there were Ro Tu Chol, vice-premier of the DPRK Cabinet, Ri Ryong Nam, minister of Foreign Trade, Kim Jong Sik, vice-chairman of the Pyongyang City People's Committee, Ri Hak Gwon, director of the DPRK Chamber of Commerce, officials in the field of foreign trade and delegations and delegates from different countries and regions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Representatives and staff members of foreign embassies here were on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Myong San, vice-minister of Foreign Trade, made a congratulatory speech at the ceremony. Then an opening address was delivered by Kim Mun Jong, president of the Korean International Exhibition Corporation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that the fair has played a great role in improving the environment of investment and business conditions of corporations and ensuring close economic cooperation among them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He reiterated the DPRK's will to strive to develop the economic exchange and cooperation with all countries friendly toward it on the principle of friendship, equality, mutual respect and reciprocity in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then, the participants went round machine tools, electrical and electronic apparatuses, petrochemicals, medicines, daily necessities, foodstuffs and other products presented by companies of the DPRK, China, Russia, Denmark, Germany, Sweden, Singapore, Australia, Austria, United Kingdom, Italy, Indonesia, Cuba, Poland and Taipei of China. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The fair will last till Sept. 25.

Film Festival Goes On before Full House 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- The 11th Pyongyang International Film Festival which opened on September 17 is going on before full house. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Full-length feature films, documentary and short films and children's films newly produced by different countries and international organizations in recent years are being screened. Some films highly appreciated at various international film festivals in the past are being specially shown at the festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Shown at the Taedongmun Cinema were such films as Chinese film "House of Flying Daggers," Italian film "Night Bus," British film "Elizabeth I," Swiss film "Vitus" and French film "Aurore." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Pyongyang International Cinema House screened foreign films including Russian film "First under God," Cuban film "Scent of Oak," Cambodian film "The Painter," Polish film "The Old Tale When the Sun Was God," Mongolian film "One Hand and Five Fingers" and Finnish film "Colorado Avenue." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dutch film "Yes Nurse! No Nurse!" Chinese Hong Kong film "Kung Fu Dunk," Jordanian film "Captain Abu Raed," Bosnia-Herzegovina film "It's Hard to Be Nice," Indian film "A Home in the Sky," Iranian film "Mainline" and others shown at the Kaeson Cinema and the Rakwon Cinema drew the interest of the cinema-goers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The films were appreciated for the truthful acting and high technique of shooting.

High Tribute to Kim Jong Suk Paid 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- Wreaths were laid before the bust of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk at the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery on Mt. Taesong on Monday on the occasion of the 59th anniversary of her demise. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seen before the bust was a wreath from Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea, chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission and supreme commander of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attending the wreath-laying ceremony were senior party, army and state officials, the chairperson of a friendly party, leading officials of party, armed forces and power bodies, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions, servicepersons and working people and schoolchildren in the city of Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Placed before the bust amidst playing of the wreath-laying music were wreaths in the name of the WPK Central Committee, the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly and the DPRK Cabinet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also laid were wreaths in the name of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions, KPA units, educational, cultural and art, public health and press organs, the joint national organizations of the Korean Children's Union, and party and power bodies, factories and farms in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants paid silent tribute to Kim Jong Suk, looking back upon her noble revolutionary life and immortal exploits. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, floral baskets were placed before her statues in Kim Jong Suk County and Hoeryong City and at Kim Jong Suk Naval Academy and Kim Jong Suk General Military School on the same occasion.

People Remember Kim Jong Suk's Brilliant Life 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- An endless stream of servicepersons, people from all walks of life and school youth and children is visiting the bust of Kim Jong Suk, an anti-Japanese war hero and woman commander of Mt. Paektu, in the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery on Mt. Taesong and the revolutionary sites and revolutionary battle sites associated with her undying feats across the country in September on the occasion of the 59th anniversary of her death. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The number of visitors reached more than 500,000 as of Sept. 21. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is a manifestation of the iron faith and will of the army and people to hold in high esteem forever Kim Jong Suk, supreme incarnation of devotedly defending the leader who gave a steady continuity to the Songun revolution and dedicated her all to the country and the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Senior party, army and state officials and over 200,000 servicepersons, people from all walks of life and school youth and children visited the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery on Mt. Taesong to pay high tribute to Kim Jong Suk. The cemetery was also visited by a great number of overseas compatriots and foreigners. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Many people of different social standings have visited the revolutionary sites in North Hamgyong Province, including the time-honored Hoeryong Revolutionary Site, Kim Jong Suk's birthplace, and revolutionary sites and revolutionary battle sites in Ryanggang, South Hamgyong and Jagang provinces, looking back with deep emotion upon her brilliant revolutionary career.

Brilliant Life of Kim Jong Suk 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- The life of anti-Japanese woman hero Kim Jong Suk was one of a lifeguard who defended the leader with her own life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She regarded it as her lifelong mission to staunchly safeguard President Kim Il Sung politically, ideologically and with her own life and lived and fought as his lifeguard till the last moments of her life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recorded in the glorious history of the President who led the army and the people along an ever-victorious path at the head of the revolution are the heroic feats performed by Kim Jong Suk who staunchly defended him on the forefront in the grimmest period of the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She covered the President with her body at crucial moments, making herself shields, in such battles as Hongqihe battle and the battle on the outskirts of Dashahe and resolutely defended and upheld his ideas and dignity through a death-defying fight against the renegade of the revolution in the Qingfeng Secret Camp in the period of the anti-Japanese armed struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With a steadfast outlook on the leader, she always devoted her all to his health and safety. She washed his clothes and dried them in her bosom in the biting cold around 40 degrees below zero and made meals for him with all sincerity even in fierce battles with the enemy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the days of building a new country, she paid special attention to the safety of the President, remaining his "bodyguard" as ever, and trained the guard personnel as his dependable bodyguards. Her devotion in this is cherished deep in the minds of the Korean people still today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The spirit of devotedly defending the leader which Kim Jong Suk handed down to the Korean people is the most precious, irreplaceable heritage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is thanks to this heritage that the slogan "Defend the leadership of the revolution headed by the great Comrade Kim Jong Il at the cost of our lives!" has become the slogan of faith and action of the whole Party, the entire army and all the people and the undisputable loyalty to the leader is throbbing in the ranks of monolithic unity with which the whole army and people long for and follow the leader unanimously.

Kim Jong Suk's Undying Feats in Cause of National Reunification 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- Anti-Japanese woman hero Kim Jong Suk performed an undying feat in the cause of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She devoted her all to the cause from the first days since the country was partitioned by foreign forces after the liberation of the country on August 15, 1945. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Having kept as her creed from early years that the victory of the revolution and the existence of the fellow countrymen were guaranteed only under the leadership of President Kim Il Sung, she conducted energetic activities for implementing his idea and line on national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Revolutionaries of south Korea crossed the military demarcation line at the risk of their lives to receive teachings from the President. She implanted his patriotic idea and intention of reunification in their minds as the pillar of the faith and led democratic figures of south Korea along the road of sacred struggle for the country and the nation with warm compatriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Immeasurable was the effort she exerted to bring up the second generation of the revolution as the pillars who would shoulder the cause of national independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She called at the Mangyongdae Revolutionary School and other centres for training revolutionary reserves to look after the students with warm affection and directed special attention to the growth of children of south Korean revolutionaries and democratic figures. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She also meticulously guided the women, who had been once humiliated and neglected, so that they would grow up as a powerful force to push one of the two wheels of reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Thanks to her energetic activities for the country's reunification, the Korean people could unite firm around the President, transcending the differences in thoughts, ideals and isms, and the reunification cause could confidently forge ahead with the President's Juche-oriented idea and line as the guideline from the first period of the struggle for achieving it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Her ardent aspiration after national reunification will be certainly realized under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il, the banner of victory and driving force in the era of independent reunification.

Agricultural and Stock-breeding Policy Protested in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- Peasants' mass actions simultaneously took place across south Korea on Sept. 19 in protest against the puppet government's unpopular agricultural and stock-breeding policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Peasants Alliance grouping the Federation of Peasants Associations and 11 other organizations held a peasants rally in Kwangju to inherit the spirit of martyr Ri Kyong Hae, win the vital rights of the peasants, check the conclusion of the FTA and protect food sovereignty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants of the rally accused the Lee Myung Bak regime of putting the stock-breeding households to a crisis through the enforcement of the policy on the import of American beef and driving the peasants to death by unilaterally controlling the prices of agricultural products at a time when the farm houses are finding themselves under heavier burdens due to the soaring prices of fertilizers and feed for domestic animals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The peasants affiliated to the South Kyongsang Provincial Alliance of the federation held a similar peasants rally in Changwon City, South Kyongsang Province while the peasants affiliated to the Kwangju and South Jolla Provincial Alliance of the federation held a rally to vow to struggle for boycotting the forwarding of agricultural products in front of the building of the South Jolla Provincial Office. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Peasants' rallies also took place in Taegu, Jonju, Suwon and other places.

60th Birthday of DPRK Marked in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- Meetings were held in Vietnam, Bangladesh and Costa Rica and meetings, film shows, art performances and book and photo exhibitions at several units of Laos between September 3 and 8 to celebrate the 60th birthday of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed in the venues of the events were works of President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il, photographs showing their immortal leadership exploits and other photographs dealing with the history of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Phat Tat Dong, chairman of the Vietnam-DPRK Friendship Association, said that the foundation of the DPRK was a historic event of weighty significance and a brilliant fruition of the heroic struggle the Korean people waged under the leadership of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rashed Khan Menon, chairman of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Bangladesh, and other speakers said that thanks to the original Songun politics pursued by Kim Jong Il who has successfully carried forward to completion the revolutionary cause of Juche pioneered by the President, the DPRK would display its dignity and might over the world and the future of the progressive mankind is bright. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jose Francisco Aguilar Bulgarelli, honorary chairman of the Latin American Institute of the Juche Idea, praised Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il for having led the DPRK to display its might as fortress of independence and socialism to the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chansamone Chanyarath, rector of the Kaysone Phomvihane Military Academy who is member of the C.C., the Lao People's Revolutionary Party, noted that the DPRK has built powerful war deterrent by directing great efforts to increasing the defence capability, thus reliably defending the national sovereignty and the socialist country and greatly contributing to the world peace and security. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Appreciated at the film shows were Korean films dealing with the President's immortal exploits in nation-building and the DPRK's invincible might. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Put on the stage of art performances were Korean songs such as "Our Hearts Yearning for the Leader", "Blue Sky over My Country" and "Arirang for Prosperity".

Week of Iran-DPRK Friendship Observed in Iran
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- A week of Iran-DPRK friendship was observed in Teheran between September 10 and 14. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed in the venue of the week-opening ceremony were works of President Kim Il Sung and General Secretary Kim Jong Il, photos showing their immortal exploits and books, photos and art works introducing Songun Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attending the ceremony were personages from political and social circles and popular masses of Iran. The ambassador and staff members of the DPRK embassy and diplomatic envoys of different countries in Iran were present on invitation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The general-director for Arts and Cultural Cooperation of the Organization of Culture and Islamic Relations of Iran said that the event held on the occasion of the 60th founding anniversary of the DPRK offers an important occasion in deepening friendship and solidarity and mutual understanding between the peoples of the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He sincerely hoped that the Korean people would register greater successes in the future under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il and that the friendly and cooperative relations between the peoples of the two countries would grow stronger. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants watched the DPRK film "HE Seyed Ali Khamenei, President of the Islamic Republic of Iran, Visits the DPRK".

Conversan delegaciones de informacion de Corea y Nepal
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 22 de septiembre (ATCC) -- Tuvieron lugar este lunes en el Palacio de los Congresos Mansudae las conversaciones entre la delegacion del Comite de Informacion de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea y la delegacion de informacion gubernamental de Nepal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En la ocasion estuvieron presentes por la parte coreana los miembros de dicha delegacion encabezada por el ministro de Cultura y presidente del Comite de Informacion, Kang Nung Su, y por la nepalesa, los integrantes de la delegacion visitante presidida por el ministro de Informacion y Comunicaciones, Krishna Bahadur Sahara.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ambas partes intercambiaron las opiniones sobre el fortalecimiento de las relaciones de amistad y cooperacion entre las entidades homologas de los dos paises y sobre otros asuntos de interes mutuo.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 La cita transcurrio en un clima amistoso.

En Iran: semana de amistad con Corea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 22 de septiembre (ATCC) -- Tuvieron lugar del 10 al 14 en Teheran las actividades por la semana de amistad Iran-Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En la sede de ceremonia inaugural de la semana estaban exhibidos las obras del Presidente Kim Il Sung y el Dirigente  Kim Jong Il, las fotos alusivas a sus imborrables hazanas y los libros, las fotos y pinturas que presentan la Corea del Songun (priorizacion militar). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En la ocasion participaron las personalidades de los circulos politico y social y los habitantes de Iran y fueron invitados el embajador coreano y otros miembros de la embajada coreana y los representantes diplomaticos de varios paises, acreditados en este pais persico. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En el acto hubo discursos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El director general de Cooperacion Artistica y Cultural de la Organizacion de Cultura y Relaciones Islamicas de Iran dijo que las actividades programadas con motivo del 60o aniversario de la fundacion de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea marcan un importante hito para fortalecer la amistad, la solidaridad y el entendimiento reciproco entre los pueblos de dos paises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Deseo de todo corazon que el pueblo coreano logre en el futuro mayores exitos bajo la sabia direccion de Su Excelencia Kim Jong Il y que se fortalezcan y se desarrollen mas las relaciones de amistad y cooperacion entre ambos pueblos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Los participantes vieron el documental coreano "Su Excelencia Seyed Ali Khamenei, presidente de la Republica Islamica de Iran, visita a Corea".
